24th |next = 26th }} The 'Twenty-fifth United States Congress' was a meeting of
the legislative branch of the United States federal government, consisting of
the United States Senate and the United States House of Representatives. It met
in Washington, D.C. from March 4, 1837 to March 4, 1839, during the first two
years of Martin Van Buren's presidency. The apportionment of seats in the House
of Representatives was based on the Fifth Census of the United States in 1830.
Both chambers had a Democratic majority.
